external_knowledge:
- "somewhat sizable" refers to lengths greater than 100mm;
- "moderate power capacity" indicates a capacity range between 1000 and 2000 mAh;
- "unique identifiers" are represented by part numbers;
- "actual sizes" refer to the lengths and capacities;
- "current stock levels" are the quantities;
- "production statuses" indicate whether the production is in progress or completed;
- "expected demand" is the predicted demand for each part.

- 'battery power' refers to the capacity of battery parts in milliampere-hours (mAh);
- 'manufacturing facilities' refers to the manufacturing sites in the data;
- The top five are determined by the average capacity of the battery parts they produce, in descending order.

sql:
SELECT part_number, delivery_date, quantity
FROM supply_chain
WHERE supplier_id > 5;

